typedef dlib::one_vs_one_decision_function<ovo_trainer,decision_function<main_kernel>> learned_function;

	std::vector<sample_type>	       samples;
	std::vector<label_type>		labels;
	ovo_trainer 				ovoTrainer; // Our one vs on trainer
	main_trainer				mainTrainer; // The main Trainer used to perform the binary classification
	main_kernel				mainKernel; 


mainTrainer.set_kernel(mainKernel);
ovoTrainer.set_trainer(mainTrainer);

ovo_decision_function decisionFunction = ovoTrainer.train(samples, labels);
dlib::save_libsvm_formatted_data("/home/a/Bureau/libsvmtrain",samples,labels);
learned_function learnedFunction;
learnedFunction = decisionFunction;

```

Like i said, i would like to get a confident score. I found probalistic_decision_function. But i didin't find a way to use it in ovo trainer.I need to make several 2-class svm and compute a confident to have a global score.

Thanks

