I am using a couple of self-made (LESS) mixins for a little while now to apply font-awesome icons to elements. 
````less
.fa-icon-content(@icon) {
  .fa-icon();
  content: @icon;
}
.fa-icon-content(@icon, @rules) {
  .fa-icon-content(@icon);
  @rules();
}
.fa-icon-before(@icon) {
  &:before {
    .fa-icon-content(@icon);
  }
}
.fa-icon-before(@icon, @rules) {
  &:before {
    .fa-icon-content(@icon, @rules);
  }
}
.fa-icon-after(@icon) {
  &:after {
    .fa-icon-content(@icon);
  }
}
.fa-icon-after(@icon, @rules) {
  &:after {
    .fa-icon-content(@icon, @rules);
  }
}
````

They can be used something like this:

````less
.sorted-table th.sort {
  .fa-icon-after(@fa-var-sort, {
    margin-left: 7px;
  });
}
.fancylink {
  .fa-icon-before(@fa-var-rocket);
}
.some-thing-which-already-has-some-after-style {
  &:after {
    .fa-icon-content(@fa-var-bus);
  }
}
